---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title={`Privacy Policy | ${SITE_TITLE}`} description="Privacy Policy and Affiliate Disclosure for PetTech." />
  </head>
  <body class="bg-white text-gray-900 font-sans">
    <Header />
    <main class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>

      <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none">
        <p><strong>Last Updated: July 20, 2026</strong></p>

        <p>At PetTech, the privacy of our visitors is of extreme importance to us. This privacy policy document outlines the types of personal information is received and collected by PetTech and how it is used.</p>

        <h2>Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
        <p>PetTech is a participant in various affiliate marketing programs. This means we may earn a commission when you click on or make purchases via affiliate links. This comes at no additional cost to you.</p>
        <p>When you click on an affiliate link, a cookie may be placed on your browser by the affiliate network to track any sales for purposes of assigning commissions. These cookies do not contain personally identifiable information.</p>

        <h2>Log Files</h2>
        <p>Like many other Web sites, PetTech makes use of log files. The information inside the log files includes internet protocol (IP) addresses, type of browser, Internet Service Provider (ISP), date/time stamp, referring/exit pages, and number of clicks to analyze trends, administer the site, track user's movement around the site, and gather demographic information. IP addresses, and other such information are not linked to any information that is personally identifiable.</p>

        <h2>Cookies and Web Beacons</h2>
        <p>PetTech does use cookies to store information about visitors preferences, record user-specific information on which pages the user access or visit, customize Web page content based on visitors browser type or other information that the visitor sends via their browser.</p>

        <h2>Consent</h2>
        <p>By using our website, you hereby consent to our privacy policy and agree to its terms.</p>
      </div>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>
